\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {11}{\ignorespaces The snake equation (compact closure axiom) rendered by DisCoPy: the left panel shows the ``snake'' diagram where a Cup contraction (epsilon) composed with a Cap expansion (eta) on adjacent wires forms a zigzag; the right panel shows the identity wire it equals. This identity---that the zigzag straightens out---is the algebraic engine powering all pregroup type reductions and justifies the cancellation steps in every DisCoCat derivation.}}{25}{figure.caption.19}\protected@file@percent }
